elong philosophical project. More than an intellectual biography or a mere charting of influence, Heidegger, Strauss, and the Premises of Philosophy is a profound consideration of these two philosophers’ reflections on the roots, meaning, and fate of Western rationalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aOntologyxHistoryx20th century. 0aOntologyxHistoryy20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Modernx20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Moderny20th century. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophyxHistoryx20th century. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophyxHistoryy20th century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226852553423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226852553.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles